<section class="container pb-5">
    <div class="problem-post">
        <div class="row align-items-center">
            <div class="col-lg-6">
                <img src="https://i0.wp.com/bankunderground.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/What-does-the-rise-in-the-inflation-mean-for-financial-stability.jpg?ssl=1" alt="Financial Stress" class="problem-img">
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-6">
                <span class="problem-tag">Financial Instability</span>
                <h3>The Income Rollercoaster</h3>
                <p class="opacity-75">
                    Unlike salaried employees, gig workers face "dry spells." A week of heavy rain or a personal illness doesn't just mean a day off—it means zero income. Traditional banks see this volatility as a "high risk," making it impossible for workers to get even small personal loans.
                </p>
                <p class="opacity-75">
                    <em>"I have the money to pay back, but because my earnings fluctuate every day, the bank rejected my application for a bike loan."</em> — <strong>Rajesh, Delivery Partner</strong>
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="problem-post">
        <div class="row align-items-center flex-row-reverse">
            <div class="col-lg-6">
                <img src="https://media.telanganatoday.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/Kothagudem-accident.jpg" alt="Medical Emergency" class="problem-img">
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-6">
                <span class="problem-tag">Health & Safety</span>
                <h3>The Cost of an Accident</h3>
                <p class="opacity-75">
                    Traffic, weather, and long hours increase the risk of accidents. Most gig workers operate without a safety net. A minor crash doesn't just damage the vehicle; it results in massive medical bills and a total loss of livelihood during the recovery period.
                </p>
                <ul class="opacity-75">
                    <li>No employer-provided health insurance.</li>
                    <li>Out-of-pocket expenses for vehicle repairs.</li>
                    <li>No sick leave benefits.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="problem-post">
        <div class="row align-items-center">
            <div class="col-lg-6">
                <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1554224155-6726b3ff858f?q=80&w=1000&auto=format&fit=crop" alt="Taxation" class="problem-img">
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-6">
                <span class="problem-tag">Compliance Gap</span>
                <h3>The Hidden Burden of Taxes</h3>
                <p class="opacity-75">
                    Managing GST, income tax, and fuel deductions is a nightmare for independent earners. Without a dedicated accountant, many gig workers overpay in taxes or face penalties simply because they didn't know how to track their expenses correctly.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

